programme.title: Sur les traces de Gerda Taro
programme.desc:
Pioneer in photojournalism, Gerda Taro (1910-1937) died young, on the front line of the Spanish Civil War. Overshadowed for many years by her partner Robert Capa, the young woman was a leading figure of antifascism and war reporting. Her name, lost from the collective memory, has recently emerged from oblivion.

Directed by: Camille Ménager (France, 2020)

Narrated by: Céline Sallette
